  "summary": "Postinstall beacon exfiltrates host info via child_process and HTTP",
  "details": "The package declares a postinstall lifecycle hook (`\"postinstall\": \"node run.js\"`) that automatically executes on `npm install`. The shipped beacon scripts (beacon19.js, beacon_linux.js) load `child_process`, `os`, and `http`, collect host identifiers via `os.hostname()` and `os.platform()`, and emit outbound HTTP GET/POST requests (`http.request(...)` with POST at beacon_linux.js line 103-104). This composition — install-time auto-execution + system reconnaissance + outbound HTTP from named files literally called `beacon*.js` — has no legitimate purpose in a package distributed under a generic `event-metrics` name. The package functions as an install-time host beacon with attacker benefit (host fingerprint collection and arbitrary command execution surface on every installer).",
